#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:97
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To play patience you need, as the name suggests, patience. For simple games, "
"where the way the game goes depends only upon how the cards fall, your "
"patience might be the only thing you need."
msgstr ""
"For at spille et kabalespil har man, som det engelske navn siger, brug for "
"tålmodighed. For enkle spil, hvor den måde spillet går på kun afhænger af "
"hvordan kortene falder, er tålmodighed det eneste man har brug for."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:103
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are also patience games where you must plan your strategy and think "
"ahead in order to win."
msgstr ""
"Men der er også kabaler, hvor man også skal planlægge en strategi og tænke "
"fremad for at vinde"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:108
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A theme common to all the games is the player must put the cards in a "
"special order &mdash; moving, turning and reordering them."
msgstr ""
"Alle spillene har det tilfælles, at man skal putte kortene i en speciel "
"rækkefølge for at flytte, vende og omarrangere dem."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:114
#, no-c-format
msgid "How to Play"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:116
#, no-c-format
msgid "Objective:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:116
#, no-c-format
msgid "Rearrange the cards by suit in as few moves as possible."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:118
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As &kpatience; offers you a multiplicity of different solitaire games, there "
"is no straightforward how-to which could fit all of them. Therefore, it is "
"essential that you read each individual subsection of Game Rules, Strategies "
"and Tips section before you start playing a version you are not familiar "
"with."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:120
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Essentially there are two types of solitaire games – the ones that let you "
"arrange the cards by same color and the ones that let you arrange the cards "
"by alternating color. You can easily determine which game you are trying out "
"using trial-and-error method. Once you know which one you are dealing with "
"the rest is easy; keep arranging and rearranging the cards and collecting "
"the matching ones."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:122
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"From the beginning, however, pay attention to your card stacks. Do not rush "
"to move individual cards around. See if it might be more useful elsewhere."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:124
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For additional help you can also take quick peeks onto the statusbar. Each "
"of the games has a built in solver which informs you whether the game you "
"are currently playing can be completed or not. If you see that solver could "
"not complete the current game, chances are you will not be able to do so as "
"well. At this point you can either restart the current game, or start a "
"completely new game."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:131
#, no-c-format
msgid "Note:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:131
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Playing solitaire games helps you to greatly improve your attention span and "
"enhance the ability to concentrate."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:134
#, no-c-format
msgid "Game Rules, Strategies and Tips"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:137
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid "General Rules"
msgstr "Generel brug"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:138
#, no-c-format
msgid "suits"
msgstr "farver"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:138
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A card game contains one or more card decks of 52 cards each. Each deck "
"contains the four suits:"
msgstr ""
"Man spiller med et eller flere spil kort af 52 kort hver. Hvert spil "
"indeholder de fire farver"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:144
#, no-c-format
msgid "Clubs"
msgstr "Klør"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:148
#, no-c-format
msgid "Spades"
msgstr "Spar"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:152
#, no-c-format
msgid "Hearts"
msgstr "Hjerter"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:155
#, no-c-format
msgid "Diamonds"
msgstr "Rudere"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:159
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each of these suits contains the following card types: ace, two, three, "
"four, five, six, seven, eight, nine, ten, jack, queen, and king."
msgstr ""
"Hver af disse fire farver indeholder følgende korttyper: es, toer, treer, "
"firer, femmer, sekser, syver, otter, nier, tier, bonde, dame og konge."

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:160
#, no-c-format
msgid "family"
msgstr "familie"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:160
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This complete order of cards is called a family. There are real families and "
"alternating ones. The real families are all of one suit (&eg; Hearts). In "
"the alternating families the card color changes from one to another, between "
"a black color (Clubs and Spades) and a red color (Hearts and Diamonds)."
msgstr ""
"Denne fuldstændige rækkefølge af kort kaldes en familie Der er rigtige "
"familier og alternerende. De rigtige er alle i samme farve (&eg; hjerter) "
"mens de alternerende familier skifter mellem en sort farve (Klør eller spar) "
"og en rød farve (Hjerter eller rudere)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:161
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid "If the family is not complete it is called a sequence."
msgstr "Hvis familien ikke er fuldstændig kaldes den en sekvens."

#. Tag: phrase
#: index.docbook:164
#, no-c-format
msgid "The game field of &kpatience;"
msgstr "Spillefeltet for &kpatience;"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:166
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are a number of features found in typical patience games. These are "
"described below."
msgstr ""
"Der er kun få forskellige elementer i et typisk kabalespil. De bliver "
"introduceret i det følgende."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:168
#, no-c-format
msgid "1. Talon"
msgstr "1. Bunken eller Talonen"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:169
#, no-c-format
msgid "talon"
msgstr "talon"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:169
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"At the beginning of each game all cards are mixed in the deck. In some games "
"not all cards are dealt out. The remaining cards are put down on the talon "
"(also called the stock). You can find this quite easily, since in most games "
"it is the only pile in which all cards are face down."
msgstr ""
"I begyndelsen af hvert spil er alle kortene blandet i kortspillet. Men det "
"er ikke i alle spil at alle kort deles ud, nogle bliver i kortspillet. Disse "
"kort puttes ned som den såkaldte bunke eller talon, som er nem at genkende, "
"da det er den eneste bunke der viser bagsiden."

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:172
#, no-c-format
msgid "2. Waste Pile"
msgstr "2. Affaldsbunken"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:173
#, no-c-format
msgid "waste pile"
msgstr "spildbunke"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:173
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Many games use a waste pile to hold cards taken from the talon. Typically "
"clicking on the talon will cause the topmost card to be flipped face up and "
"placed on the waste pile, at which point the card enters play."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:176
#, no-c-format
msgid "3. Foundation"
msgstr "3. Grundlagsbunker"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:177
#, no-c-format
msgid "foundation"
msgstr "grundlagsbunke"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:177
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The foundation piles are where you want your cards to end up. Typically, the "
"game is won only once all cards have been moved to the foundation piles in "
"the correct order. The number of foundation piles and the ordering required "
"varies from game to game."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:178
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Most games start with the foundation piles empty. Choosing the "
"<guimenuitem>Drop</guimenuitem> action from the menu or toolbar will cause "
"&kpatience; to scan through all the piles move as many cards to the "
"foundation piles as it can. If you have the <guimenuitem>Enabled Autodrop</"
"guimenuitem> setting activated, &kpatience; will attempt to perform a drop "
"whenever possible."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: index.docbook:181
#, no-c-format
msgid "4. Playing Piles"
msgstr "4. Spillebunker"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:182
#, no-c-format
msgid "playing piles"
msgstr "spillebunker"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:182
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These piles are those where the actual reordering happens. The rules for "
"these piles vary a lot between games. Some show all cards on them, some do "
"not. Some allow only one card to be removed, some allow every card to be "
"removed, &etc;"
msgstr ""
"Disse bunker er de eneste hvor en egentlig omordning sker. Reglerne for "
"disse bunker varierer meget mellem spillene. Nogle viser alle korttene i "
"dem, nogle gør ikke. Nogle tillader kun at kort fjernes, nogle tillader et "
"vilkårligt kort bliver fjernet, osv. Se de følgende kapitler for detaljer."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:188
#, no-c-format
msgid "Rules for Individual Games"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:191
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Klondike</title>"
msgstr "<title>Klondike</title>"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:193
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>Klondike</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Klondike</primary>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:193
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Klondike is the most famous patience &mdash; most likely because it comes "
"with a well-known operating system. It is played with one deck."
msgstr ""
"Klondike er den mest berømte kabale - formodentlig fordi et ofte "
"brugtoperativ system kommer med den. Den spilles med ét spil kort."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:198
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The goal in Klondike is to put all cards, as real families, ascending on the "
"foundation. This gets easier once all cards are lying face up in the playing "
"piles."
msgstr ""
"Formålet med Klondike er at putte alle kortene som rigtige familier og "
"stigende på grundlaget. Dette virker sædvanligvis temmelig godt så snart "
"alle kortene har forsiden opad i spillebunkerne."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:204
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The sequences on the playing piles have to be put there in descending order. "
"The cards should alternate in colors (red and black). You can move whole "
"sequences or parts of it, if the first card fits on another pile."
msgstr ""
"Sekvenserne i spille bunkerne skal være i aftagende rækkefølge og med "
"alternerende farver (rød og sort). Man kan flytte en hel sekvens eller dele "
"af den hvis første kort passer på en anden bunke."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:210
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On a free pile you can put a king of any color, or a sequence starting with "
"a king."
msgstr ""
"På en fri bunke kan man lægge en vilkårlig konge, eller en sekvens der "
"starter med en konge."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:215
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you click on the talon, one card from it will be moved to the waste "
"pile. You can move it to the playing piles or the foundation from there. If "
"the talon is empty, you can move the complete waste pile to the talon by "
"clicking on the empty talon."
msgstr ""
"Når man klikker på talonen, vil et kort der fra blive flyttet til "
"affaldsbunken, hvorfra man kan flytte den til en af spillebunkerne eller "
"grundlaget. Hvis talonen er tom, kan man flytte hele affaldsbunken op på "
"talonen ved at klikke på den tomme talon."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:222
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can look through the cards on the talon as much as you like."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:228
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Grandfather</title>"
msgstr "<title>Bedstefar</title>"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:230
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>Grandfather</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Bedstefar</primary>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:230
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This game was introduced to &Paul-Olav.Tvete;, the original developer of "
"&kpatience;, by his grandfather; it is named after this. No other patience "
"games are known to implement this patience game variant."
msgstr ""
"Dette spil blev introduceret til Paul af hans bedstefar, så derfor navnet. "
"Der er ikke andre kendte kabalespil der implementerer denne kabale"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:235
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In Grandfather, one deck is dealt to seven playing piles. Some cards on each "
"pile are face down on the initial deal."
msgstr ""
"Bedstefar deler et spil kort ud i syv spillebunker. Nogle kort på hver bunke "
"har forsiden nedad i den oprindelige uddeling."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:240
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The goal is to put all cards as real families ascending on the foundation "
"piles."
msgstr ""
"Målet er at få alle kortene i rigtige familier, stigende, over på "
"grundlagsbunkerne."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:244
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can move every card on every pile if it fits on another card, to build a "
"real sequence of descending order. For example, you can move the five of "
"spades on top of the six of spades, no matter how many cards on are on top "
"of the five of spades. Just the six of spades has to be on top of its pile."
msgstr ""
"Man kan flytte hvert kort på hver bunke, hvis det passer til et andet kort "
"til at bygge en sekvens i aftagende rækkefølge. For eksempel kan man flytte "
"spar fem hen ovenpå spar seks, ligegyldigt hvor mange kort der er ovenpå "
"spar fem. Spar seks derimod skal være på toppen af sin bunke."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:251
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On a free pile you can place a king (again no matter how many cards are on "
"top of it)."
msgstr ""
"På en fri bunke kan man placere en konge (igen ligegyldigt hvor mange kort "
"der er ovenpå den)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:256
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If there are no more possible moves, you can redeal the cards. A redeal "
"consists of picking up the cards from the playing piles (pile by pile, left "
"to right) and redealing them in the starting pattern (zigzagging rows of "
"face down cards forming a peak and then left to right rows of face up cards "
"on top). Note that the cards are <emphasis>not</emphasis> shuffled and that "
"cards on the foundation piles are left untouched. You may redeal no more "
"than twice in a single game."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:265
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Even though the rules are simple and allow many moves, the game is still "
"hard to win. Despite this, or because of it, this game remains a joy to play."
msgstr ""
"Selvom reglerne er simple og tillader en del træk, er det alligevel svært at "
"vinde spillet, men det er stadigvæk morsomt at spille (måske netop derfor)."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:272
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Aces Up</title>"
msgstr "<title>Esser op</title>"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:274
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>Aces Up</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Esser op</primary>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:274
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This patience has simple rules, yet is hard to win. It is played with one "
"deck. The goal is to put all cards besides aces onto the foundation. There "
"should be an ace left on every playing pile afterwards."
msgstr ""
"Denne kabale har meget enkle regler, med den er alligevel svær at vinde. Den "
"spilles med et spil kort og målet er at få alle kort undtagen esserne over "
"på grundlaget. Til sidst skal der kun være et es tilbage på hver spillebunke."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:280
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Each top card that is of the same suit (&eg; spades) and has a lower value "
"than another top card (&eg; six of spades and four of spades) can be put on "
"the foundation by clicking on it."
msgstr ""
"Hvert top kort der er af samme farve (&eg; spars) og har en lavere værdi end "
"et andet top kort (&eg; spar seks og spar fire) kan puttes over på "
"grundlagsbunken ved at klikke på det."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:286
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you cannot move any more cards to the foundation, you can get a new card "
"for each playing pile by clicking on the talon."
msgstr ""
"Hvis man ikke kan flytte flere kort over på grundlaget, kan man tage et nyt "
"kort for hver spillebunke fra talonen."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:291
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"On a free pile you can move every other card on top of a pile. You should "
"use these moves to free piles. That way, new cards can be moved to the "
"foundation."
msgstr ""
"Man kan flytte ethvert kort fra toppen af en bunke hen på en fri bunke. Man "
"bør vælge disse træk til frie bunker på en sådan måde at nye kort kan "
"flyttes hen  på grundlaget bagefter."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:296 index.docbook:384
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid "The auto drop feature is disabled in this patience game."
msgstr "Auto drop egenskaben er deaktiveret for denne kabale."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:303
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Freecell</title>"
msgstr "<title>Fricelle</title>"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:305
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>Freecell</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Fricelle</primary>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:305
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Freecell is played with one card deck. You have four free cells in the top "
"left corner. In addition there are four foundation piles, and eight playing "
"piles below."
msgstr ""
"Fricelle spilles med et spil kort. Man har fire frie celler i øverste "
"venstre hjørne. Ved siden af er der fire grundlagsbunker og nedenfor det er "
"der otte spillebunker."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:310
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The goal of the game is to have all cards as real families ascending on the "
"foundation. You can achieve this often if you know how to play: Freecell is "
"solvable at a rate of 99.9% approximately &mdash; of the first 32,000 deals "
"there is only one unsolvable (11,982 if you want to know)."
msgstr ""
"Spillets formål er at få alle kort i rigtige familier og tiltagende på "
"grundlaget. Dette virker ganske ofte hvis man ved hvordan man skal spille "
"idet fricelle er løsbart i 99.9% af tilfældene nogenlunde (af de første "
"32000 uddelinger er  der kun en ikke løsbar - 11982 hvis du gerne vil vide "
"det)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:317
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the playing piles you have to build descending sequences, where red and "
"black cards alternate. You can put any card in a free cell."
msgstr ""
"I spillebunkerne skal man bygge nedadgående sekvenser, hvor man skifter "
"mellem røde og sorte kort. I en fri celle kan man putte et vilkårligt kort."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:322
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can only move one card that lays on top of a pile or a free cell. "
"Sequences can only be moved if you have enough free space (either free cells "
"or free playing piles) to place the cards."
msgstr ""
"Man kan kun flytte et enkelt kort der ligger på toppen af en bunke eller en "
"fri celle. Sekvenser kan kun flyttes hvis man har nok fri plads (frie celler "
"eller frie spillebunker) til at putte kortene i mellemtiden."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:328
#, no-c-format
msgid "The maximum amount of cards you can move is calculated by:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:332
#, no-c-format
msgid "(#{free cells} + 1) * 2<superscript>#{free piles}</superscript>"
msgstr "(#{frie celler} + 1) * 2<superscript>#{frie bunker}</superscript>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:336 index.docbook:599 index.docbook:631
#, no-c-format
msgid "Variations:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:338
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<quote>Baker's Game</quote> is like <quote>Freecell</quote>, but the piles "
"are built down by suit."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:339
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<quote>Eight Off</quote> is like <quote>Freecell</quote>, but the piles are "
"built down by suit. You have 8 reserves and only kings can fill empty "
"spaces. Four reserves are filled at game start."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:340
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<quote>Forecell</quote> is like <quote>Freecell</quote>, but the reserves "
"are filled at game start, and only kings can fill empty spaces."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:341
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<quote>Seahaven Towers</quote> is like <quote>Freecell</quote>, but with 10 "
"piles which are built down by suit, and only kings can fill empty spaces. "
"Two reserves are filled at game start."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:344
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To solve this game it is recommended to grab the cards out of the playing "
"sequences in the same order they have to be put into the foundation (first "
"the aces, then the twos, &etc;)"
msgstr ""
"For at løse dette spil anbefales det at tage kortene ud af spillesekvenserne "
"i samme rækkefølge som de skal puttes ind i grundlaget (først esser, så "
"toere, &etc;)"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:350
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You should try to keep as many free cells and/or playing piles empty, so you "
"can build sequences as long as possible."
msgstr ""
"Man bør forsøge at holde så mange frie celler og/eller spillebunker tomme "
"som muligt, så man kan bygge så lange sekvenser som muligt."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:358
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Mod3</title>"
msgstr "<title>Mod3</title>"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:360
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>Mod3</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Mod3</primary>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:360
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Mod3 is played with two card decks. The goal is to put all cards on the top "
"three rows. In those you have to build sequences of the same color. In the "
"first row you have to create the sequence 2-5-8-J, in the second row the "
"sequence 3-6-9-Q, and in the third row the sequence 4-7-10-K. The suit of "
"the cards must be the same in each sequence, so you can only put a five of "
"hearts on top of a two of hearts."
msgstr ""
"Mod-3 spilles med to spil kort uden esser. Målet i spillet er at putte alle "
"kortene i de øverste tre rækker. I disse skal man bygge sekvenser af samme "
"farve. I den første række skal man lave sekvensen 2-5-8-B, i den anden række "
"sekvensen 3-6-9-D og i den tredje række sekvensen 4-7-10-K. Man skal følge "
"kulør i hver sekvens, så man kan putte hjerter fem ovenpå hjerter 2."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:369
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The fourth row is both your waste pile and playing pile. On an empty slot "
"you can put any card from the first three rows, or one from the top of the "
"fourth row."
msgstr ""
"Den fjerde række er samtidig affaldsbunke og spillebunke. På en tom plads "
"kan man putte et vilkårligt kort fra de første tre rækker eller en på toppen "
"af den fjerde række."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:374
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can put aces on the aces piles, on top of the talon. They are in the "
"game so you have a starting point for creating free slots."
msgstr ""
"Esser du kan putte på es-bunkerne på toppen af talon. De er i spillet så du "
"har  et startpunkt til at lave frie pladser."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:379
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you cannot move any more cards, you can get new cards on the fourth row "
"by clicking on the talon."
msgstr ""
"Hvis man ikke kan flytte flere kort, kan man få nye kort i den fjerde række "
"ved at klikke på talonen."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:390
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "<title>Mod3</title>"
msgid "<title>Normandy</title>"
msgstr "<title>Mod3</title>"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:392
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "<primary>Mod3</primary>"
msgid "<primary>Normandy</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Mod3</primary>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:392
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Normandy is played with two card decks. The aim is to put all cards in real "
"families ascending on the foundation."
msgstr ""
"Sigøjner spilles med to spil kort. Målet i spillet er at putte alle kortene "
"i rigtige familier der er stigende på grundlagsbunkerne."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:397
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The playing piles have to be descending, while red and black cards have to "
"alternate. You can only move sequences or single cards. On a free slot you "
"can put any card or sequence."
msgstr ""
"Spillebunkerne skal være aftagende med skiftevis røde og sorte kort. Man kan "
"kun flytte sekvenser eller enkelte kort. På en fri plads kan man putte et "
"vilkårligt kort eller sekvens."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:403
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you cannot move any more cards, you can click on the talon to get new "
"cards on each playing pile."
msgstr ""
"Hvis man ikke kan flytte flere kort, kan man klikke på talonen for at få en "
"ny bunke kort på hver spillebunke."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:407
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In using the <guibutton>Undo</guibutton> feature you can ease the game quite "
"a lot, as you have to take many decisions and some of them might turn out to "
"be wrong after you clicked the talon."
msgstr ""
"Ved at bruge fortrydefunktionen gør man spillet en hel del lettere da man "
"kan lave beslutninger og nogen af dem viser sig at være forkerte efter man "
"har klikket på talonen"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:413
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This game is also known under the name \"Gypsy\", but because this term is "
"considered derogatory and offensive by many, we have chosen to use the "
"alternative name \"Normandy\" instead."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:421
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Forty &amp; Eight</title>"
msgstr "<title>Otte og fyrre</title>"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:423
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>Forty &amp; Eight</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Otte og fyrre</primary>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:423
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Forty &amp; Eight is played with two card decks. The goal is to put all "
"cards as real families on the foundation."
msgstr ""
"Otte og fyrre spilles med to spil kort. Målet i spillet er at putte alle "
"kortene i grundlagsbunkerne som rigtige familier"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:428
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The playing piles have to be descending. Colors are important. You can only "
"put a five of hearts on a six of hearts, for example."
msgstr ""
"Spillebunkerne skal være aftagende, men man skal bekende kulør. Så man kan "
"kun putte hjerter fem på hjerter seks."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:433
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can only move one card on top of a pile. You can put any card in a free "
"slot."
msgstr ""
"Man kan kun flytte et enkelt kort hen på toppen af en bunke. På en fri plads "
"kan man putte et vilkårligt kort."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:437
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"By clicking on the talon you can put a card on the waste pile; from there "
"you can put it on a playing pile or the foundation (&kpatience; will do this "
"for you). If the talon is empty you can put all cards on the waste pile back "
"on the talon. This works only once: after the second time the talon empties, "
"the game is over."
msgstr ""
"Ved at klikke på talonen kan man putte et kort på affaldsbunken, hvorfra man "
"kan putte det på en spillebunke eller grundlagsbunke (Det sidste gør "
"&kpatience; for dig). Hvis talonen er tom kan man putte alle kortene fra "
"affaldsbunken tilbage på talonen. Dette virker kun én gang, efter talonen er "
"tom for anden gang er spillet forbi."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:444
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This patience is difficult to solve. With some experience you can solve many "
"of the deals, especially if you use the <guibutton>Undo</guibutton> feature "
"from time to time to correct your decisions, and the decisions &kpatience; "
"makes in putting cards on the foundation."
msgstr ""
"Denne kabale er ikke særlig nem at løse, men med lidt erfaring, kan man  "
"løse mange spil, især hvis man bruger fortryde funktionen en gang imellem "
"til at rette sine beslutninger, og de beslutninger &kpatience; laver om at "
"putte kort på grundlagsbunkerne."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:453
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Simple Simon</title>"
msgstr "<title>Simple Simon</title>"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:455
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>Simple Simon</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Simple Simon</primary>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:455
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Simple Simon is played with one card deck. The goal is to put all cards as "
"real families on the foundation."
msgstr ""
"Simple Simon spilles med et spil kort. Målet i spillet et at putte alle "
"kortene som rigtige familier på grundlagsbunkerne."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:460
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the playing piles you can build sequences. In general you don't have to "
"care about the suits of the cards, but sequences can only be moved if they "
"are part of a real sequence. For example, you can move the six of spades if "
"the five of <emphasis>spades</emphasis> is on top of it, but may not move it "
"if the five of <emphasis>clubs</emphasis> is on top of it."
msgstr ""
"I spillebunkerne kan man bygge sekvenser. I almindelighed behøver man ikke "
"bekymre sig om kortenes kulør, men sekvenser kan kun flyttes hvis de er en "
"del af en rigtig sekvens (&eg; man kan kun flytte spar seks hvis den har "
"spar fem ovenpå, ikke hvis den har klør fem ovenpå)."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:468
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The cards can only be moved to the foundation if all 13 cards of one family "
"lay on top of each other in the playing piles."
msgstr ""
"Kortene kan kun flyttes til en grundlagsbunke hvis alle 13 kort i en familie "
"ligger på toppen af hinanden i spillebunkerne."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:474
#, no-c-format
msgid "Suggestion"
msgstr "Forslag"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:475
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You should try as soon as possible to move the cards to the correct piles, "
"to create free piles to place cards on temporarily, since you can put any "
"card on those."
msgstr ""
"Man skal prøve så tidligt som muligt at flytte kortene væk fra bunkerne til "
"højre for at få frie bunker til at placere kort på midlertidigt, da man kan "
"putte disse kort et vilkårligt sted"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:480
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With enough free room you can build families on free slots independently of "
"the color. If you have all cards in such families you can sort them by "
"color, so they can be moved to the foundation."
msgstr ""
"Med nok friplads kan man bygge familier på frie pladser uafhængig af farven. "
"Hvis man har alle kort i sådanne familier kan man sortere dem efter deres "
"farve, så de kan flyttes til grundlagsbunkerne."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:489
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Yukon</title>"
msgstr "<title>Yukon</title>"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:491
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>Yukon</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Yukon</primary>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:491
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Yukon is played with one card deck. The goal is to put all cards as real "
"families ascending on the foundation."
msgstr ""
"Yukon spilles med et spil kort. Målet i spillet er at putte alle kortene som "
"rigtige familier stigende på grundlagsbunkerne."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:496
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The sequences on the playing piles have to be descending with alternating "
"red and black cards. You can move every face up card no matter how many "
"cards are on top of it. So you can put a five of hearts on a six of spades "
"if that one is on top of its pile."
msgstr ""
"Sekvenserne på spillebunkerne skal være aftagende med skiftevis røde og "
"sorte kort. Man kan flytte ethvert kort med forsiden opad uanset hvor mange "
"kort der ligger ovenpå det. Så man kan flytte en hjerter fem på en spar "
"seks, hvis denne er på toppen af sin bunke."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:502
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "In a free slot you can put a king of any color (again, no matter how many "
#| "cards are on top of it)"
msgid ""
"In a free slot you can put a king of any color (again, no matter how many "
"cards are on top of it)."
msgstr ""
"På en fri plads kan man putte en konge af en vilkårlig farve (igen uanset "
"hvor mange kort der er ovenpå det)"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:509
#, no-c-format
msgid "Grandfather's Clock"
msgstr "Bedstefars ur"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:511
#, no-c-format
msgid "Grandfathers Clock"
msgstr "Bedstefars ur"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:511
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Grandfather's clock is a simple patience game. With some experience you "
"should be able to solve most deals. It is played with one card deck. The aim "
"is to put the cards as real ascending sequences on the foundation."
msgstr ""
"Bedstefars ur er en simpel kabale, og efter nogle eksperimenter skulle man "
"være i stand til at løse de fleste spil. Det spilles med et spil kort og "
"formålet med spillet er at putte kortene som rigtige stigende sekvenser på "
"grundlagsbunkerne."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:517
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The foundation is on the right-hand side and consists of 12 piles that form "
"the shape of a clock. The nine is at 12 o'clock, the queen is at 3 o'clock, "
"the three is at 6 o'clock and the six is at 9 o'clock."
msgstr ""
"Grundlagsbunkerne er i højre side og består af 12 bunker i form som et ur. "
"Esset er klokken et, bonden klokken 11 og dronningen klokken 12."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:523
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are 8 playing piles beside the clock and on each are 5 cards. On the "
"playing piles you can build descending sequences. The color of the cards is "
"not important. You can only move one card at a time."
msgstr ""
"Der er 8 spillebunker ved siden af uret og på hver af dem er 5 kort. På "
"spillebunkerne kan man bygge aftagende sekvenser uden at bekymre sig om "
"kortenes farve. Man kan kun flytte et kort af gangen."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:532
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Golf</title>"
msgstr "<title>Golf</title>"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:534
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>Golf</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Golf</primary>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:534
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Golf is played with one card deck. The goal of Golf is to move all the cards "
"on the tableau to the foundation."
msgstr ""
"Golf spilles med en dæk kort. Formålet med Golf er at flytte alle kortene i "
"udlægningen til grundkortene."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:537
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The layout of golf solitaire is straightforward. At the beginning of the "
"game you will see the tableau. On it are seven columns each containing five "
"cards. The talon and the foundation are below."
msgstr ""
"Layout i kabalen Golf er ligetil. I begyndelsen af spillet ser du "
"udlægningen, hvor der er syv søjler som hver indeholder fem kort. Derunder "
"findes talonen og grundkortene."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:541
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Playing golf solitaire is simple, but requires strategy to win. The cards at "
"the base of each column on the tableau are available for play. Available "
"cards are built upon the top foundation card in ascending or descending "
"sequence regardless of suit. If there are no moves available a card may be "
"dealt from the talon to the foundation. The game is over when all the cards "
"in the talon have been dealt and there are no more possible moves."
msgstr ""
"At spille kabalen Golf er enkelt, men der kræves strategi for at kunne "
"vinde. Kortene længst nede i hver søjle i udlægningen er tilgængelige for "
"spil. Tilgængelige kort bygges på det øverste grundkort i stigende eller "
"faldende sekvens, uafhængig af farve. Hvis ingen forflytninger er mulige kan "
"et kort deles ud fra talonen til grundkortet. Spillet er slut når alle kort "
"i talonen er delt ud, og ingen yderligere forflytninger er mulige."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:550
#, no-c-format
msgid "<title>Spider</title>"
msgstr "<title>Edderkop</title>"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:552
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>Spider</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Edderkop</primary>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:552
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Spider is played with two card decks. The cards are dealt out into 10 "
"playing piles, 4 of 6 cards and 6 of 5 cards each. This leaves 50 cards that "
"can be dealt out 10 at a time, one on each playing pile."
msgstr ""
"Edderkop spille med to spil kort. Kortene uddeles i 10 spillebunker, 4 med 6 "
"kort og 6 med 5 kort hver. Dette efterlader 50 kort der kan uddeles 10 af "
"gangen, en på hver spillebunke."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:558
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "In the playing piles, a card can be placed on another card of any suit "
#| "and of one higher value. A sequence of ascending cards of the same suit "
#| "may be moved from one playing pile to another."
msgid ""
"In the playing piles, a card can be placed on another card of any suit and "
"of one higher value. A sequence of descending cards of the same suit may be "
"moved from one playing pile to another."
msgstr ""
"I spillebunkerne, kan et kort  placeres ovenpå et andet kort af vilkårlig "
"farve og én højere værdi. En sekvens af stigende kort i samme farve kan  "
"flyttes fra en spillebunke til en anden."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:564
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The goal of spider is to put all cards as real families descending from "
"Kings anywhere in the playing piles. When such a family is built in a "
"playing pile, it is removed to the lower-left corner of the window."
msgstr ""
"Målet i edderkop er at putte alle kort i rigtige familier der går nedad fra "
"Konger hvorsomhelst i spillebunkerne. Når sådan en familie er lavet i en "
"spillebunke, fjernes den til det nederste hjørne tilvenstre i vinduet."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:570
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The different levels determine how many suits are dealt - Easy uses 1 suit, "
"Medium uses 2 suits, and Hard uses all 4 suits. The game is fairly easy to "
"win at Easy level, and very difficult to win at Hard level."
msgstr ""
"De forskellige niveauer afgør hvor mange farver der uddeles - Nem bruger 1 "
"farve, Middel bruger 2, og vært bruger alle 4 farver. Spillet er ret nemt at "
"vinde som  Nemt, og meget vanskeligt som Svært."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:579
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "<title>Yukon</title>"
msgid "<title>Baker's Dozen</title>"
msgstr "<title>Yukon</title>"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:581
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "<primary>Yukon</primary>"
msgid "<primary>Baker's Dozen</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Yukon</primary>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:581
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Baker's Dozen is played with one card deck. The game's name originates from "
"the 13 columns in the game, the number in a baker's dozen. The cards are "
"dealt into columns of four on the tableau, resulting in 13 columns. Any king "
"that is in the top or middle of each column must be placed on the bottom "
"before the game starts. Two kings that are mixed into one column are placed "
"on the bottom without changing their order."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:590
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The object of the game is to build all the cards onto the four foundations "
"by suit, each from ace to king"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:594 index.docbook:626
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the playing piles you have to build descending sequences, regardless of "
"suit. You can only move one card that lays on top of a pile."
msgstr ""
"I spillebunkerne skal man bygge nedadgående sekvenser, hvor man skifter "
"mellem røde og sorte kort. I en fri celle kan man putte et vilkårligt kort."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:601
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In <quote>Spanish Patience</quote>, any card can fill empty tableau spaces. "
"(In some sources, the foundations are built up regardless of suit)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:602
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<quote>Castles in Spain</quote> is akin to <quote>Spanish Patience</quote>, "
"but the cards in the tableau are built down by alternate color. In some "
"variations, the tableau is dealt face-down aside from the top cards of each "
"column."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:603
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<quote>Portuguese Solitaire</quote> is halfway between <quote>Baker's Dozen</"
"quote> and <quote>Spanish Patience</quote> because empty columns can only be "
"filled with Kings."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:606
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "To solve this game it is recommended to grab the cards out of the playing "
#| "sequences in the same order they have to be put into the foundation "
#| "(first the aces, then the twos, &etc;)"
msgid ""
"To solve this game it is recommended to grab the cards out of the playing "
"sequences in the same order they have to be put into the foundation (first "
"the aces, then the twos, &etc;) Typically, you want to avoid emptying a "
"column until the last card is ready to be moved to a foundation."
msgstr ""
"For at løse dette spil anbefales det at tage kortene ud af spillesekvenserne "
"i samme rækkefølge som de skal puttes ind i grundlaget (først esser, så "
"toere, &etc;)"

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:616
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "<title>Golf</title>"
msgid "<title>Castle</title>"
msgstr "<title>Golf</title>"

#. Tag: primary
#: index.docbook:618
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid "<primary>Golf</primary>"
msgid "<primary>Castle</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>Golf</primary>"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:618
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Castle is a family of patience or solitaire card games typically played with "
"a deck of 52 playing cards. It is sometimes described as \"Freecell without "
"cells\" because its game play is similar but without extra empty spaces to "
"maneuver in most variations."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:622
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The object of the game is to build all the cards onto the four foundations "
"by suit, each from ace to king."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:633
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<quote>Beleaguered Castle</quote>. Aces are dealt to the foundations. Any "
"card can fill empty spaces."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:634
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<quote>Citadel</quote> is like <quote>Beleaguered Castle</quote>, but "
"matching cards are moved to the foundation during the deal, leaving uneven "
"piles."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:635
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<quote>Exiled Kings</quote> is like <quote>Citadel</quote>, but only kings "
"can fill empty spaces."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:636
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<quote>Siegecraft</quote> is like <quote>Beleaguered Castle</quote>, but "
"with one free cell."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:637
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<quote>Streets and Alleys</quote> is like <quote>Beleaguered Castle</quote>, "
"but aces are included in shuffling."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:638
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<quote>Stronghold</quote> is like <quote>Streets and Alleys</quote>, but "
"with one free cell."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:641
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To solve this game it is recommended to build evenly on the foundations. Try "
"to create empty piles which can be used to facilitate longer moves to free "
"up buried cards."
msgstr ""

